u} \approx 0$, since both the electron and the neutrino have negligible rest mass compared with the proton rest mass $m_{p}$.

In the lab frame, the two protons have the same energy $\gamma m_{p}$ and impact angle $	heta$, and the electron is at rest. Calculate the energy $E_{
